30. Be3 Bxe3 31. fxe3 Rd3 32. Rxb7 Rxe3 33. Rxa7 {1/2-1/2 (33) Adams,M (2731)
-Lputian,S (2634) Moscow 2004 I believe both sides can improve along the way})
(18. g4 $5 {is my recommendation here although 18.Bd2 is pleasant too} g5 19.
Qh2 Nd6 20. Qg2 Nc4 (20... Bd7 21. h4) 21. h4 N4e5 22. Nxe5 Nxe5 23. Nd4 {
